var APhi = '<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="slide-caption-hidden"><h1>THE BEAUTY AND POWER OF SISTERHOOD</h1><p>Alpha Phi is a sisterhood of outstanding women supporting one another in lifelong achievement. Our mission is to continue to live by our values of sisterhood, scholarship, service, leadership, loyalty and character development.</p></div><div id="slide-container"><div id="slideshow-images"><!-- THE CONTENT OF THE SLIDESHOW IS CONTROLLED BY slideShow.js --></div><div class="slide-caption"><h1>THE BEAUTY AND POWER OF SISTERHOOD</h1><p>Alpha Phi is a sisterhood of outstanding women supporting one another in lifelong achievement. Our mission is to continue to live by our values of sisterhood, scholarship, service, leadership, loyalty and character development.</p></div></div><div class="container marketing"><div class="row" id="quote-row"><div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 quote-col" id="quote-one"><div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-12"><img class="img-circle" src="_includes/images/pictures/13559056_10210088475197172_4140235152872775708_o.jpg" alt="Catherine and Christina"></div><div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-12"><p class="quote-mark">I joined Alpha Phi because each and every woman I met made me feel at home. I knew I had found my future best friends.”</p></div></div><div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 quote-col"><div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-12"><img class="img-circle" src="_includes/images/pictures/12359981_1045885055453571_7824281231089330244_n.jpg" alt="Jill and Olivia"></div><div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-12"><p class="quote-mark">I feel privileged to be part of such an amazing organization of women who are as passionate as I am.”</p></div></div><div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 quote-col"><div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-12"><img class="img-circle" src="_includes/images/pictures/14195305_10210578235880794_2218277366166579872_o.jpg" alt="Marol and Loewen"></div><div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-12"><p class="quote-mark">Through joining Alpha Phi, I met my best friends, my biggest inspirations and the women who shape my life.”</p></div></div></div><!-- /.row --><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-sm-7 col-md-8"><h2 class="featurette-heading">Letter From the President</h2><p class="lead">Welcome to Alpha Phi at MIT! It is truly my honor to introduce the amazing women of our sorority. The Zeta Phi chapter represents MIT’s first sorority founded in 1984 by a group of accomplished and driven young women looking to create a unique community at MIT. As members, we strive to uphold their legacy by sharing a commitment to excellence, to our community both at MIT and in Boston, and to each other.</p><p class="lead">From our froyo cravings, bachelor obsessions, and fitness fads, these are the girls that I laugh with, study with, and grow with. We cheer each other on at NCAAs, Dance Troupe performances, and Boston marathons. Our sisterhood goes beyond our attendance at each other’s events; these are the girls that will always be my shoulder to cry on or ear to complain to and offer their thoughts and support. They are the people that help me make important decisions and guide me through the struggles of MIT. I would not be on my career path today without the guidance and help of my sisters. The tutoring I received and review sessions I attended my freshman year helped me adapt to MIT’s demanding academics and I am happy to return the favor now as an upperclassman. With struggle comes victory and we are always celebrating a new job offer, grad school admittance, or internship at every chapter. We have Harvard Med School students, Marshall Scholars, Google Product Managers, and Bain Consultants.</p><p class="lead">Outside of our sisterhood and scholarship, I have never met a group of women so committed to philanthropy and serving our Boston community. Every year, our sisters commit to the Alpha Phi Foundation in support of Women’s Heart Health by participating in two major philanthropy events. We hold Red Dress Gala in the fall during Parent’s Weekend and King of Hearts, a male beauty pageant, in the spring. Outside of our philanthropy, we host monthly community service events such as volunteering at the Boston Marathon, walking in the September Boston Heart Walk, and, my favorite, holding our Relay for Life fundraiser Mac n Phis. Besides within our sorority, sisters never fail to astonish me in their various community service achievements and roles in leadership. From Girl Scout Gold Awards, to presidents of major service clubs such as SHINE for Girls and Camp Kesem, as well as leaders in other student group such as Class Council and the UA, our commitment to our community goes beyond Alpha Phi.</p><p class="lead">These girls have made me the woman I am today. I have truly found paradise at Alpha Phi and can’t imagine college without my sisters.</p><p class="lead pull-right">AOE, <span class="signature">Emily Benz</span></p></div><div class="col-sm-5 col-md-4"><img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="_includes/images/pictures/12004979_939215152812677_1561775090072791697_n.jpg" style="margin-bottom:15px"> <img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="_includes/images/pictures/0_crop.jpg" style="margin-bottom:15px"> <img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="_includes/images/pictures/12771472_10208944608121121_1214235693070065282_o.jpg"></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div><script src="_includes/js/slideShow.js"></script><script src="_includes/js/indexSlides.js"></script></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><span class="navlink-current">About Us </span>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">About Us</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/11143091_10206589731530678_4936720778597148939_o.jpg"><p class="lead">Alpha Phi was founded on October 10, 1872 by a group of ten forward thinking young women looking to create a social center for women at Syracuse University. The women were ten of the first twenty women admitted to Syracuse. Since its founding, Alpha Phi has flourished and grown to include over 150 chapters throughout the United States and Canada and remains the strong sisterhood and support network that our founders intended to create.</p><p class="lead">The Syracuse founders were leaders on their college campus and not unlike the founders of our Zeta Phi chapter here at MIT which was founded on February 11, 1984 marking the the creation of the first Panhellenic sorority at MIT. The founding members included sixty-four accomplished, driven, and social women who similarly were looking to create a special bond between like minded women at MIT.</p><p class="lead">Today, that bond remains strong. Our purpose is to create an environment that encourages support, scholarship, service, and sisterhood in all that we do. We love eating dinners together, holding review sessions for classes, volunteering at Fenway Park and for the Boston Marathon, hosting distinguished alumni in our home, and even going on boat trips for sisterhood retreats. We encourage all members to grow and achieve to their fullest capacity during their time at MIT and beyond and support each other in all that we do.</p></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<span class="navlink-current"> Philanthropy and Service </span>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Philanthropy and Service</h2><div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-9"><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/12309749_913617348693396_1211654070728425663_o.jpg"><p class="lead">As members of Alpha Phi, we pride ourselves in giving back to both the MIT campus and Boston community. Our interests are diverse and varied, which can be observed by the plethora of events that we are involved in. Find us handing out water and cheering on runners at the Boston Marathon. Spot us mentoring elementary school girls interested in engineering. Catch us sorting cans at the Boston Food Bank or walking in the Postural Orthostatic Tachycardia (POTS) 5k. Alpha Phi members contribute personal time and efforts to national causes such as Women’s Heart Health, Relay for Life, Dysautonomia awareness, and more.</p></div><div class="col-sm-3 col-xs-hidden"><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/red-dress-photobooth.jpg"></div></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-sm-7"><h2 class="featurette-heading">Red Dress Gala</h2><p class="lead">In October during Family Weekend, the Zeta Phi chapter of Alpha Phi at MIT holds our annual Red Dress Gala. The evening includes food, speeches, student group performances, and a talent show featuring our sisters. In addition to revenues from the tickets, we facilitate a silent auction and raffle, in which all proceeds are donated to the Alpha Phi Foundation in support of women’s heart health, our philanthropy. The funds help to increase awareness and education in our community and beyond. This special occasion allows us to take pride in Alpha Phi and share our philanthropic values with all of our family and friends, while dressed in red in honor of spreading awareness for our cause.</p></div><div class="col-sm-5"><img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="/_includes/images/pictures/1412807_10201177024204645_787361229_o.jpg"></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-sm-7 col-sm-push-5"><h2 class="featurette-heading">King of Hearts</h2><p class="lead">King of Hearts is an annual male pageant show that raises money for women"s heart health, Alpha Phi"s philanthropy cause. Aside from being our largest fundraising event of the semester, King of Hearts also brings together the MIT community as the contestants represent their fraternities, living groups, or sports teams. This year"s event will take place on April 30th, and the contestants will try their luck for the title of King of Hearts!</p></div><div class="col-sm-5 col-sm-pull-7"><img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="/_includes/images/koh/2.jpg"></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-sm-7"><h2 class="featurette-heading">Mac "N" Phis</h2><p class="lead">Pasta, anyone? Mac "N" Phis is an annual philanthropic event in which 100% of its proceeds go towards the MIT Relay for Life fundraiser. The sisters of Alpha Phi make an assortment of pasta dishes and open the house to visitors for a buffet-style meal.</p></div><div class="col-sm-5"><img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="/_includes/images/pictures/macandcheese.jpg"></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<span class="navlink-current"> Campus Involvement </span>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Campus Involvement</h2><!-- <img class="marketing-header-img" src="pictures/campus/sports/sherry.png"> --><div id="slide-container" style="margin-bottom:15px"><div id="slideshow-images"><!-- THE CONTENT OF THE SLIDESHOW IS CONTROLLED BY slideShow.js --></div></div><p class="lead">Our sisters are extremely involved on campus. Sisters are competitive athletes on 14 of the 16 varsity teams. We have sisters on the class of 2016, 2017, and 2018 Class Councils including the President of the Class of 2017. Sisters serve as key members of the Undergraduate Associate including the Head of the Finance Board and Student Support and Mental Health Committee. In addition to campus government, MIT Alpha Phi members lead community service groups as the President of groups such as SHINE for Girls and Globemed. In the arts, Alpha Phi members include the Vice President of Dance Troupe, lead singers in Resonance A Cappella Group, and Producers of our student plays and musicals.</p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Athletics</h2><p class="lead" id="athletics-holder"></p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Academic Organizations</h2><p class="lead" id="academics-holder"></p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-6"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Performance Groups</h2><p class="lead" id="performance-holder"></p></div><div class="col-md-6"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Cultural and Religious Organizations</h2><p class="lead" id="cultural-religious-holder"></p></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div><script src="/_includes/js/slideShow.js"></script><script src="/_includes/js/campusSlides.js"></script><script src="/_includes/js/campusInvolvement.js"></script></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<span class="navlink-current"> Recruitment </span>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Recruitment</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/11218065_954867527889602_2368092732098904187_n.jpg"><!-- <p class="lead"><b> 5/8/16 Update: </b> <a href="https://mit.mycampusdirector.com/register/" target="_blank">Registration for Fall Recruitment 2016 is now open!</a></p> --><p class="lead">Alpha Phi is so much more than a sorority. It is more than a group to study with, a group to smile with, or a group to make memories with. Alpha Phi about the way we look at each other and know exactly what is going through our minds. It is the crazy pictures and inside jokes that make us laugh for no reason. It is the moments we laugh so hard we cry. This is why we are inseparable. This is why Alpha Phi is more than a sorority—it is a sisterhood.</p><p class="lead">At Alpha Phi, we pride ourselves on our commitment to academic enrichment, our pursuit of personal goals, our passion for philanthropic involvement, and our constant development of genuine friendships. As Alpha Phi’s Vice President of Membership Recruitment, it is my honor and privilege to welcome you to Greek life at MIT and introduce you to our incredible sisterhood. The opportunities here at Alpha Phi have allowed me to grow as a student, a leader, and, most importantly, as a person. I have found a home at Alpha Phi, and I cannot wait to help you find that home during Recruitment in September! Recruitment is all about finding the house that will enhance your time at MIT, while providing you with friendships that will last a lifetime.</p><p class="lead pull-right">AOE, <span class="signature">Emma Chesley</span></p></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<span class="navlink-current"> Scholarship </span>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Scholarship</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/scholarship2.jpg"><p class="lead">The Zeta Phi chapter has always put an emphasis on scholarship and the ability of the chapter to help its members be successful in this area. Our chapter has worked to help our members excel in academics, such as the Scholarship Big/Little Program, frequent review sessions run by upperclassmen, sharing of advice regarding class scheduling, study environments conducive to learning without distraction, rewarding members who attend classes regularly, and recognizing those who have made outstanding scholastic achievements. The Scholarship Big/Little program maintains that the semester after a new member has declared a major, they are matched with an upperclassman in the same major or field of study. This program is unique to our chapter and is something that members continually voice their appreciation of.</p><p class="lead">In addition to providing members with multiple resources for learning material, studying for exams, and obtaining advice, the Zeta Phi chapter helps to maintain the positive attitude that is critical for scholastic achievement. The chapter leaders help to emphasize the importance of being productive and staying motivated, while remembering to take breaks and share one’s accomplishments with friends.</p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Companies Sisters Have Worked For</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/bretl-nasa.jpg"><p class="lead" id="company-images"></p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Labs Sisters Have Worked In</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/cynthialab.jpg"><p class="lead" id="lab-names"></p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Awards Sisters Have Received</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/12747861_1290796727600828_2695671159687731328_o.jpg"><p class="lead" id="award-names"></p></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div><script src="/_includes/js/companies.js"></script></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<span class="navlink-current"> Sisterhood </span>|<a href="/alumni" class="navlink"> Alumni</a></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Sisterhood</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/10985241_10203875006943677_1029357929772375975_n.jpg"><p class="lead">Sisterhood is, without a doubt, central to Alpha Phi.</p><p class="lead">We bond together. When new members are welcomed into our family they are immediately matched with a Big Bear – an Alpha Phi senior there to help them through their first year and serve as a loving role model. Later an arguably even closer connection is made when one is matched with their Big - there to inspire, mentor, and just to hang out and eat froyo with. Additionally, we are proud to be the only sorority on campus to offer an academic Scholarship Big and Little relationship to guide sisters through their major at MIT. These Alpha Phi friendships last a lifetime.</p><p class="lead">We relax together. Sisterhood events, carefully planned by our hard-working Sisterhood Committee, give us a chance to take a well-deserved break from MIT with fun activities. Sometimes it’s tie-dyeing on the Esplanade near the Alpha Phi house, other times enjoying sushi and sweet treats while watching movies in the cozy confines of our chapter room. In the fall, sisters look forward to traditions including a spooky Halloween get-together and a huge Thanksgiving potluck dinner with plenty of Martinelli’s.</p><p class="lead">We celebrate each other. In weekly chapter meetings we nominate “Fit Phi of the Week” to appreciate all our athletes and sisters staying healthy, “Smarty Pants” for academic achievement of all kinds, and “Sister of the Week” for any other outstanding accomplishments. At the end of the school year seniors are celebrated with a week of family line gift giving. At the end of the week they receive letters from sisters that got to know and appreciate them throughout the years and have a special senior event with only their Alpha Phi class.</p><p class="lead">Above all, we support each other. The concept of Watchcare, part of our core Alpha Phi values, encourages support through the highs and lows of life.</p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Class Of 2020</h2><div class="col-sm-12" id="members-2020"></div></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Class Of 2019</h2><div class="col-sm-12" id="members-2019"></div></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Class Of 2018</h2><div class="col-sm-12" id="members-2018"></div></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Class Of 2017</h2><div class="col-sm-12" id="members-2017"></div></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div><script src="/_includes/js/members.js"></script></body></html><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>MIT Alpha Phi</title><base href="aphi.mit.edu"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/bootstrap/css/carousel.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="/_includes/css/slide-imgs.css" rel="stylesheet"><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico"></head><body><header><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mitaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/facebook.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://www.instagram.com/mitalphaphi/" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/instagram.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="https://twitter.com/MITAlphaPhi" target="_blank"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/twitter.png" class="social-media-icon"></a><a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu"><img src="/_includes/images/icons/email.png" class="social-media-icon"></a></header><a href="http://aphi.mit.edu" class="aphi-title">Alpha Phi</a><p class="school-title">Massachusetts Institute of Technology | Zeta Phi Chapter</p><div class="line-divider"><a href="/about" class="navlink">About Us </a>|<a href="/philanthropy" class="navlink"> Philanthropy and Service </a>|<a href="/campus" class="navlink"> Campus Involvement </a>|<a href="/recruitment" class="navlink"> Recruitment </a>|<a href="/scholarship" class="navlink"> Scholarship </a>|<a href="/sisterhood" class="navlink"> Sisterhood </a>|<span class="navlink-current"> Alumni</span></div><div class="container marketing"><!-- START THE FEATURETTES --><div class="row featurette singleton"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Alumni</h2><img class="marketing-header-img" src="/_includes/images/pictures/13312878_10154339749782859_3615584962481452114_n.jpg"><p class="lead">Dear Alumni of the Zeta Phi Chapter of Alpha Phi</p><p class="lead">Welcome to our updated website! We hope that our the information provided here helps enable you to meet current sisters, reconnect with alumni sisters, reminisce over old memories, and find ways to be involved in MIT Alpha Phi.</p><p class="lead">Be sure to join the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/235174683345886/">MIT Alumni Facebook group</a> and update your contact information through the <a href="https://alum.mit.edu/home">Infinite Connection</a> if you haven’t already! We are also in the process of creating and updating our class mailing lists. If you do not believe that you are on your respective mailing list, please do not hesitate to reach out to us!</p><p class="lead">In addition, the chapter now sends out newsletters every semester. For your convenience, we have included the most recent version below to keep you up to date with the chapter! We have also included upcoming events that we would love to see you at.</p><p class="lead">We truly believe that once an Alpha Phi, always an Alpha Phi. No matter where life has taken you since MIT, the Zeta Phi chapter will always welcome you home with open arms.</p><p class="lead pull-right" style="text-align:right">AOE, <span class="signature">Elisa K. and Katherine M.</span><br>Vice President of Marketing | Director of Parent and Alumni Relations</p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">25th House Anniversary</h2><p class="lead">September 23-25, 2016</p><p class="lead">In September we will be celebrating the 25th Anniversary of our Chapter"s house. Our home today holds 61 sisters across the sophomore, junior, and senior classes and is a place for studying, sleeping, and having fun! We would like to invite all alumni to join the reunion, taking place on the afternoon of September 24th. We are planning to open the house around noon so you can tour our beautiful property, followed by a celebratory luncheon in Kenmore Square.</p><p class="lead">Please save the date, and let us know if you are able to attend by emailing <a href="mailto:tafeyan@gmail.com">tafeyan@gmail.com</a>.</p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Red Dress Gala</h2><p class="lead">October 29, 2016</p><p class="lead">This October, we will be holding our Fifth Annual Red Dress Gala. We will have dinner, speeches, music, and plenty of raffle and silent auction items! All proceeds will benefit the Alpha Phi Foundation in support of women’s heart health. If you would like more information or are interested in donating, please <a href="mailto:aphiexec16@mit.edu">contact us</a>!</p><p class="lead">Be sure to save the date! We can’t wait to see you again!</p></div></div><div class="row featurette"><div class="col-md-12"><h2 class="featurette-heading nomargin">Alpha Phi News</h2><object data="/alumni/newsletter/2016-04-MIT-APh-NL.pdf" type="application/pdf" width="100%" height="500"><p class="lead">Your browser does not support pdfs, <a href="alumni/2016-04-MIT-APh-NL.pdf">click here to download the file.</a></p></object></div></div><!-- /END THE FEATURETTES --><!-- FOOTER --><footer><p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p><p>© 2016 MIT Alpha Phi</p></footer></div><!-- /.container --><!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript================================================== --><!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster --><script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"></script><script>window.jQuery||document.write("<script src="/_includes/index_files/jquery.min.js"><\/script>")</script><script src="/_includes/index_files/bootstrap.min.js"></script><!-- IE10 viewport hack for Surface/desktop Windows 8 bug --><script src="/_includes/index_files/ie10-viewport-bug-workaround.js"></script><span style="height:20px;width:40px;position:absolute;opacity:1;z-index:8675309;display:none;cursor:pointer;border:none;background-image:url(&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;);background-color:transparent;background-size:40px 20px"></span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="500" height="500" viewBox="0 0 500 500" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="display:none;visibility:hidden;position:absolute;top:-100%;left:-100%"><defs><style type="text/css"></style></defs><text x="0" y="25" style="font-weight:700;font-size:25pt;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,Open Sans,sans-serif">500x500</text></svg><div id="point-jawn" style="z-index:2147483647"></div></body></html>';